{"id":58799,"date":"2024-08-27T11:33:00","date_gmt":"2024-08-27T06:03:00","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/?p=58799"},"modified":"2024-08-29T11:49:18","modified_gmt":"2024-08-29T06:19:18","slug":"small-apartment-balcony-ideas","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/home-interiors\/small-apartment-balcony-ideas\/","title":{"rendered":"Stunning Small Apartment Balcony Ideas to Inspire Eclectic Homes"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p><em>Making the most out of a small apartment balcony idea is about creating a perfect combination of visual appeal and comfort.<\/em><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Searching for some small balcony apartment design ideas? You have come to the right place.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>A small apartment balcony should ideally continue your indoor design choices into the outdoor space. It provides you with an avenue for conversation with your neighbours and serves as a canvas for putting your entire creative vision to life. The balcony floor needs to allow for a seamless transition between the indoors and outdoors. Hence, you need to consider factors like structural stability, sturdiness, weather and water resistance, aesthetic appeal, the amount of maintenance required, budget, and more to arrive at the perfect <a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/guides\/balcony-flooring\/\">balcony flooring<\/a> material for your apartment.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Let\u2019s dive into the most Instagrammable small apartment balcony ideas out there. We\u2019re sure that many of these will appeal to you. Read on!<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Apartment Small Balcony Garden Idea With Nature&#8217;s Vibes<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>This small apartment balcony with garden vibes is definitely a treat for sore eyes. The wooden frame furniture with comfy cushions, the green elements in the form of potted plants at various heights, and the green grass wall make this a perfect spot for dining under the stars with your loved ones. The <a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/home-interiors\/balcony-bar-ideas\/\">mini-bar unit<\/a> on the right end also makes a unique addition to the space. Protect the space with a foolproof roof for weather safety.&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/08\/29114143\/small-apartment-balcony-garden-ideas.jpg\" alt=\"Small apartment balcony garden ideas for a natural vibe\" class=\"wp-image-58804\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/08\/29114143\/small-apartment-balcony-garden-ideas.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/08\/29114143\/small-apartment-balcony-garden-ideas-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/08\/29114143\/small-apartment-balcony-garden-ideas-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/08\/29114143\/small-apartment-balcony-garden-ideas-50x30.jpg 50w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/08\/29114143\/small-apartment-balcony-garden-ideas-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">Cosy cushions brighten the area<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"mbgc-slide-caption\"><a href=\"#contactUsModal\" data-toggle=\"modal\"><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"img-fluid\" alt=\"Make way for high end balcony design trends\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/15143758\/make-way-for-high-end-balcony-design-trends.jpg \" \/><\/a><\/div>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Apartment Very Small Balcony Design With a Mini Bar Unit<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>This small apartment <a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/interior-design\/balcony-design\/\">balcony design<\/a> comes with artificial grass flooring so that you have a homely yet refreshing padding for all those bare feet at a fraction of the actual cost. The floor is complemented by the sunny yellow multifunctional zone\u2014a reading nook, bench with built-in storage, tiny office station, and sliding-doored mini-bar unit. Who wouldn\u2019t want to spend their time here on a breezy day? Just add a roll-up blind for privacy.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/08\/29114132\/small-apartment-balcony-ideas-with-bar.jpg\" alt=\"Small apartment balcony ideas with a mini bar unit to enjoy your evening\" class=\"wp-image-58803\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/08\/29114132\/small-apartment-balcony-ideas-with-bar.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/08\/29114132\/small-apartment-balcony-ideas-with-bar-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/08\/29114132\/small-apartment-balcony-ideas-with-bar-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/08\/29114132\/small-apartment-balcony-ideas-with-bar-50x30.jpg 50w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/08\/29114132\/small-apartment-balcony-ideas-with-bar-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">Add some cool recess lights to enjoy your evenings<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Small Apartment Balcony Ideas on a Budget: Use Privacy Panel<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>If your balcony is starved of space, you can still convert it into a simple, tranquil haven with this small apartment private balcony idea. Install a rattan two-seater sofa and a rattan coffee table to bring a rustic and natural vibe to the space. You have a fixed jali-design privacy panel on one side that will protect you from the sunny rays and you can even slide the door on the other end to create a secluded meditation zone for yourself.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/08\/29114120\/budget-small-apartment-balcony-ideas.jpg\" alt=\"Small apartment balcony ideas on a budget with ambient lighting\" class=\"wp-image-58802\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/08\/29114120\/budget-small-apartment-balcony-ideas.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/08\/29114120\/budget-small-apartment-balcony-ideas-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/08\/29114120\/budget-small-apartment-balcony-ideas-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/08\/29114120\/budget-small-apartment-balcony-ideas-50x30.jpg 50w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/08\/29114120\/budget-small-apartment-balcony-ideas-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">Add a pendant light or sconce for ambient lighting<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Small Apartment Balcony With Smart Furniture Like A Multifunctional Cabinet<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>This small apartment\u2019s <a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/home-interiors\/balcony-decoration-ideas\/\">balcony decor ideas<\/a> look stunning. It features a horizontal, low-lying, multifunctional cabinet with shelving units for displaying and storing your knickknacks. The cabinet acts as a striking feature against the wooden accent wall. The top of the cabinet can also double up as a serving area. The peacock blue garden chairs, the wall art, and the artificial grass rug add elegance to the space.&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/08\/29114109\/small-apartment-balcony-ideas-with-smart-furniture.jpg\" alt=\"Small apartment balcony ideas with potted plants for a creative look\" class=\"wp-image-58801\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/08\/29114109\/small-apartment-balcony-ideas-with-smart-furniture.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/08\/29114109\/small-apartment-balcony-ideas-with-smart-furniture-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/08\/29114109\/small-apartment-balcony-ideas-with-smart-furniture-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/08\/29114109\/small-apartment-balcony-ideas-with-smart-furniture-50x30.jpg 50w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/08\/29114109\/small-apartment-balcony-ideas-with-smart-furniture-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">Hang potted plants to balance privacy and creativity<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"mbgc-slide-caption\"><a href=\"#contactUsModal\" data-toggle=\"modal\"><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"img-fluid\" alt=\"Space saving balcony spaces for an aesthetic vibe!\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/02\/27114809\/space-saving-balcony-spaces-for-an-aesthetic-vibe-scaled.jpg \" \/><\/a><\/div>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Small Apartment Balcony Lighting Ideas<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>This small apartment <a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/home-interiors\/balcony-lighting-ideas\/\">balcony with fancy lights<\/a> would definitely entice you to leave work early because it is so attractive and has a welcoming vibe. It features a designer bookshelf for displaying all your favourite novels with a few drawers for additional storage. The pouffes, the circular rug, and the armchair give you an option for seating as per your mood. The lantern, artificial candle lights, and sconces exude a sense of opulence.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/08\/29114056\/small-apartment-balcony-lighting-ideas.jpg\" alt=\"Small apartment balcony lighting ideas for a fancy look\" class=\"wp-image-58800\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/08\/29114056\/small-apartment-balcony-lighting-ideas.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/08\/29114056\/small-apartment-balcony-lighting-ideas-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/08\/29114056\/small-apartment-balcony-lighting-ideas-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/08\/29114056\/small-apartment-balcony-lighting-ideas-50x30.jpg 50w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/08\/29114056\/small-apartment-balcony-lighting-ideas-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">Use a weatherproof privacy panel on the balcony<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Wrapping Up<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Here&#8217;s hoping these small apartment balcony ideas on a budget have led you to consider your next apartment balcony redesigning\/renovation project. With some creativity and effort, you can convert your overlooked outdoor space into a functional and stylish oasis that you\u2019ll proudly call your own. So, what are you waiting for? Get the ball rolling. <a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/contact-us\/\">Reach out to DesignCafe<\/a> if you need a kickstart, and we\u2019ll gladly help you out.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">FAQs On Small Apartment Balcony Ideas<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>How do you make a small apartment balcony look big &amp; beautiful?<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Add a wall mirror to reflect light and make the space look brighter.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Choose lightweight, folding and open-frame furniture instead of bulky furniture.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Install some raised planters, over-rail balcony planters or fit shelving for wall planters.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Use colourful cushions, soft lighting, and comfortable seating for an inviting atmosphere.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>How do you create privacy in your small apartment balcony without obstructing the view?<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Install bamboo screens, a wooden frame or a Tetris-patterned partition on either side of the balcony.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Consider measures like childproof locks and a sturdy high railing for homes with children.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Suspend hanging planters in a row or put up pendant\/strip lights to camouflage the view.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Put outdoor curtains or roll-up shades on your balcony to regulate the sunlight and privacy.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>How do you maximise the space in a very small apartment balcony idea?<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Install sliding doors with glass panels to create a brilliant inside-outside connection.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Add multifunctionality by using the balcony as a play area, home bar, reading nook, etc.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Create a built-in comfortable seating arrangement with storage capabilities to up its worth.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Extend the same flooring material that is inside the house to the outside space, too.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"row blog-form\">\n\t<div class=\"offset-lg-3 col-lg-6 bg-light\">\n<fieldset class=\"field-set\">\n<!-- <legend align=\"left\"> -->\n                    \n    <h3 class=\"widget-title text-dark text-center mb-0\">Looking For Functional Interior Designs?<\/h3>\n  \n \n     <p class=\"text-center text-dark mt-0\"> Get 20% extra space with smart solutions<\/p>\n    <!-- <\/legend> -->\n<form id=\"blogContactUsFormMain\" action=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.co